						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: <hi rend="italic">Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēsarivarman</hi> ie., (Parāntaka I). Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>Built in. This inscription records a gift of 40 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold tested by the touch-stone of the <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> by a native of Eṭṭiyār Kuṟichchi in Panḍi-nāḍu, in order to feed a learned brāhmāṇa (well-versed in vēdas) for reciting before the deity of Tiruvoṟṟiyūr. This gift was probably invested on land as there is a reference to <hi rend="italic">kaṇṇāṟu-aiñjupaṭṭi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
